Sentencas: A perovskite La1-xSrxMnO3 cathode thin film for an oxygen ion conducting solid oxide fuel cell was prepared using a low power (8.8 kW) liquid solution plasma spray method.
Titulo: Study of the La1-xSrxMnO3 Cathode Film Prepared by a Low Power Plasma Spray Method with Liquid Solution Precursor for a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Usually, a 30-50 kW Ar plasma torch with temperature higher than all the melting points of solid precursors is essential to synthesis oxides thin film.
Titulo: Study of the La1-xSrxMnO3 Cathode Film Prepared by a Low Power Plasma Spray Method with Liquid Solution Precursor for a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: However, using the liquid precursors as the feeding materials, the required power can be reduced and save a lot of thermal budget.
Titulo: Study of the La1-xSrxMnO3 Cathode Film Prepared by a Low Power Plasma Spray Method with Liquid Solution Precursor for a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The precursors are water solutions of lanthanum nitrate hexahydrate, manganese(II) nitrate tetrahydrate, and strontium nitrate.
Titulo: Study of the La1-xSrxMnO3 Cathode Film Prepared by a Low Power Plasma Spray Method with Liquid Solution Precursor for a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The atomic percentage of La in the plasma sprayed La1-xSrxMnO3 cathode film is lower than that of La in the feeding precursor into the torch, which is due to the low boiling temperature of La(NO3)(3) precursor.
Titulo: Study of the La1-xSrxMnO3 Cathode Film Prepared by a Low Power Plasma Spray Method with Liquid Solution Precursor for a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The oxygen stoichiometry of La1-xSrxMnO3-delta deduced from the valence state of Mn measured by X-ray absorption spectroscopy shows an oxygen deficit structure.
Titulo: Study of the La1-xSrxMnO3 Cathode Film Prepared by a Low Power Plasma Spray Method with Liquid Solution Precursor for a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The measured low resistivity of 0.07-0.09 omega cm at room temperature for this La1-xSrxMnO3-delta is essential for oxygen ion transport in the cathode thin film of a solid-state fuel cell.
Titulo: Study of the La1-xSrxMnO3 Cathode Film Prepared by a Low Power Plasma Spray Method with Liquid Solution Precursor for a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
